				<h1 itemprop="headline" class="entry-title">Rival Bids for Family Dollar Stores as Retailers Fight to Sell to Working Poor</h1>
		<div class="story-meta-footer">
			<address class="byline author vcard" itemprop="author creator" itemtype="//schema.org/Person">
				By Michael J. de la Merced and Nelson D. Schwartz			</address>
			<!-- date published --><time class="dateline " datetime="2014-08-18T10:39:06+00:00" itemprop="datePublished">August 18, 2014 6:39 am</time>
			<!-- date updated --><span class="visually-hidden updated">August 18, 2014 6:39 am</span><button class="button comments-button  theme-kicker" data-skip-to-para-id="">
</button>
		</div>
			</header>
		<div class="entry-content">
	<div class="w592"><figure class="promo media video blog-video "
    data-videoid="100000003061152" data-media-action="modal" data-autoplay="" data-embedded="true" aria-label="media" role="group">
        <span class="visually-hidden">Video</span>

    <figcaption class="caption">
        <h4 class="headline">Dollar General Bids for Family Dollar</h4>
		        <div class="caption-video">
                <div class="summary-credit">
            <p class="summary">Andrew Ross Sorkin examines the emergence of an unsolicited $8.9 billion takeover bid that promises a potential clash over the fate of Family Dollar.</p>
            <span class="credit video-credit" itemprop="copyrightHolder">
